Program: The History Hour
Title: The Death of Princess Diana
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/w3csv0w4
Last Broadcast Date: Sun 3 Sep 2017
Princess Diana's brother remembers the passionate speech he gave at her funeral, and one of the doctors who treated her at the scene of her fatal car crash remembers her death. Plus, how George Orwell wrote Animal Farm, the development of a revolutionary new 3D medical scanning technique, and the birth of the online auction site eBay. Picture: Earl Spencer and Prince William at Princess Diana's funeral. Credit: Getty/AFP Show less